So currently, the most popular one to achieve 100% crit is, {{item:3087}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3031}} 

Or some people still take 10% Crit Chance in Runes and instead go {{item:3087}} {{item:3031}} 
 
But I wanna talk about some other builds. Why is Statik Shiv SPECIFICALLY core on Yasuo? Why not {{item:3046}} {{item:3031}} ? You&#039;re still achieving 100% Crit Chance but you&#039;re not sacrificing the early game by having to take Crit Reds in your runes and you&#039;re reaching your biggest power spike, an item earlier. Allowing you to go for a bigger range of items afterwards like {{item:3035}} {{item:3072}} {{item:3153}} {{item:3139}} 

Or, {{item:3087}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3031}}? Also getting 100% Crit, but you&#039;re getting some more neat stats and a cool active.

I&#039;m not an expert on Yasuo at all, but please, discuss!
